4:T1ffd,<h2>Why Pennsylvanians Are Moving to Tampa Bay</h2>
<p>Pennsylvania's 3.07% flat income tax is low compared to neighbors like New Jersey and New York, but many PA cities add local earned income taxes (1–3.75% in Philadelphia). Property taxes are above national averages, winters are cold and gray, and the cost of living in the Philadelphia and Pittsburgh suburbs continues to climb. Tampa Bay offers zero income tax, no city taxes, warmer weather, and a lifestyle upgrade that has steadily drawn PA families south.</p>
<p>This page covers the statewide Pennsylvania perspective. If you're specifically in the Philadelphia area, also check our <a href="/moving-from/moving-from-philadelphia/">Moving from Philadelphia</a> guide for city-specific details.</p>
<h2>Cost of Living Comparison</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Category</th>
<th>Pennsylvania</th>
<th>Tampa Bay</th>
<th>Difference</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Median home price</td>
<td>$290,000</td>
<td>$400,000</td>
<td>+38%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>State income tax</td>
<td>3.07% flat</td>
<td>0%</td>
<td>-100%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Local income tax</td>
<td>1–3.75%</td>
<td>0%</td>
<td>-100%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>1BR apartment rent</td>
<td>$1,100–$1,800</td>
<td>$1,500–$1,800</td>
<td>+0–35%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Groceries</td>
<td>103 (index)</td>
<td>103 (index)</td>
<td>Similar</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Homeowners insurance</td>
<td>$900–$1,500/yr</td>
<td>$2,500–$5,000/yr</td>
<td>Much higher</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Heating costs</td>
<td>$1,500–$3,000/yr</td>
<td>$0</td>
<td>-100%</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Tampa Bay is more expensive for housing and insurance. The tax savings, elimination of heating costs, and lifestyle upgrade justify it for most transplants. For Pittsburgh-area families looking at affordable Tampa Bay counties like <a href="/counties/hernando/">Hernando</a> or <a href="/counties/polk/">Polk</a>, the housing gap narrows significantly.</p>
<h2>Tax Savings Breakdown</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Household Income</th>
<th>PA State + Local Tax</th>
<th>FL State Tax</th>
<th>Annual Savings</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>$75,000</td>
<td>$3,050–$5,100</td>
<td>$0</td>
<td>$3,050–$5,100</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$100,000</td>
<td>$4,070–$6,820</td>
<td>$0</td>
<td>$4,070–$6,820</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>$150,000</td>
<td>$6,105–$10,230</td>
<td>$0</td>
<td>$6,105–$10,230</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><em>Higher end includes Philadelphia's 3.75% wage tax. Lower end is suburban PA with minimal local tax.</em></p>
<p>Pennsylvania has an inheritance tax (4.5–15% depending on beneficiary relationship). Florida has none.</p>
<h2>Culture Shock and Lifestyle Differences</h2>
<h3>Central PA / Pittsburgh vs. Eastern PA</h3>
<p>Pennsylvania is really two states culturally. Pittsburgh and central PA share midwestern sensibilities — friendly, humble, sports-obsessed. Philadelphia and its suburbs are more Northeast — direct, fast-paced, opinionated. Tampa Bay absorbs both types well, but the adjustment is different. Pittsburghers feel instantly at home with Tampa Bay's friendly vibe. Philadelphians may need a month to decompress.</p>
<h3>The Outdoor Lifestyle Shifts</h3>
<p>Pennsylvania has beautiful hiking — the Appalachian Trail, Poconos, and Allegheny National Forest. Tampa Bay is flat but trades mountain trails for beaches, springs, kayaking, and fishing. If your outdoor identity is trail-based, you'll need to build a new routine around water-based activities. Most people find the swap rewarding.</p>
<h3>Winter Disappears</h3>
<p>Pennsylvania winters range from "manageable" in the southeast to "brutal" in the north and west. Lake-effect snow in Erie, ice storms in Harrisburg, gray skies everywhere. Tampa Bay eliminates all of it. The first time you spend January in shorts grilling in your backyard, you'll wonder why anyone lives in a cold climate voluntarily.</p>
<h2>Best Tampa Bay Areas for PA Transplants</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pittsburgh suburbs</strong> → <a href="/cities/brandon/">Brandon</a> / <a href="/cities/riverview/">Riverview</a> in <a href="/counties/hillsborough/">Hillsborough County</a> — affordable family suburbs, friendly community</li>
<li><strong>Lehigh Valley / Lancaster</strong> → <a href="/cities/wesley-chapel/">Wesley Chapel</a> or <a href="/cities/land-o-lakes/">Land O' Lakes</a> in <a href="/counties/pasco/">Pasco County</a> — growing suburbs, new construction</li>
<li><strong>State College / central PA</strong> → <a href="/cities/lakeland/">Lakeland</a> in <a href="/counties/polk/">Polk County</a> — small-city vibe, college-town energy (thanks to USF and Florida Southern)</li>
<li><strong>Poconos / rural PA</strong> → <a href="/cities/spring-hill/">Spring Hill</a> or <a href="/cities/brooksville/">Brooksville</a> in <a href="/counties/hernando/">Hernando County</a> — affordable, quieter pace</li>
</ul>
<h2>The Move Itself</h2>
<p>Pennsylvania to Tampa Bay is <strong>900–1,200 miles</strong> depending on your location — <strong>14–18 hours</strong> of driving.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Professional movers:</strong> $3,500–$7,000</li>
<li><a href="https://www.pods.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">PODS Moving &#x26; Storage</a> — $2,500–$5,000</li>
<li><a href="https://www.uhaul.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">U-Haul</a> — $1,200–$2,800</li>
<li><strong>Route from Pittsburgh:</strong> I-79 → I-77 → I-26 → I-95 → I-4 (or I-77 → I-26 → I-95 → I-10 → I-75)</li>
<li><strong>Route from eastern PA:</strong> I-95 South through D.C. corridor</li>
</ul>
<h2>Setting Up Your New Life</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Auto insurance</strong> — <a href="https://www.policygenius.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">Policygenius</a> for Florida rates.</li>
<li><strong>Driver's license and registration</strong> — 30-day deadline. See <a href="/pillar/florida-drivers-license/">FL guides</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Internet</strong> — <a href="https://www.spectrum.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">Spectrum Internet</a> primary. <a href="https://www.t-mobile.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">T-Mobile Home Internet</a> alternative.</li>
<li><strong>Home security</strong> — <a href="https://www.adt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">ADT Home Security</a> or <a href="https://www.simplisafe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">SimpliSafe</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Handyman</strong> — <a href="https://bestbayservices.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">Best Bay Services — Handyman &#x26; Home Services</a> for settling in.</li>
<li><strong>Homestead exemption</strong> — January 1 – March 1. See <a href="/pillar/florida-homestead-exemption/">guide</a>.</li>
</ol>
<h2>FAQ</h2>
<h3>Is Sheetz or Wawa in Florida?</h3>
<p>Wawa has expanded into Florida with locations in the Tampa Bay area. Sheetz has not. Score one for the eastern PA crowd.</p>
<h3>Can I keep my Steelers/Eagles loyalty?</h3>
<p>Absolutely. Tampa Bay has bars for every NFL fan base. Steelers bars are particularly plentiful — the Steelers Nation travels well. Eagles fans are also well-represented thanks to the Philly-to-Tampa pipeline and Phillies spring training in <a href="/cities/clearwater/">Clearwater</a>.</p>
<h3>How does the healthcare compare?</h3>
<p>Tampa Bay has world-class facilities: Tampa General (Level 1 trauma), Moffitt Cancer Center (nationally ranked), Johns Hopkins All Children's. See our <a href="/pillar/tampa-bay-healthcare/">Healthcare guide</a>. It rivals Pittsburgh's UPMC system and Philadelphia's hospital corridor.</p>
<p><em>Ready to make the move? Barrett Henry has been helping families relocate to Tampa Bay for over 23 years. <a href="https://nowtb.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">The NOW Team — Barrett Henry, REALTOR®</a></em></p>
